Just know I'm also thinking that. This is the compiled erb template code (beautyfied a little):

``` ruby
def _app_cells_product_form_show_html_erb__2110851674852849489_70010274372100(local_assigns, output_buffer)
  _old_virtual_path, @virtual_path = @virtual_path, "product_form/show"
  _old_output_buffer = @output_buffer

  @output_buffer = output_buffer || ActionView::OutputBuffer.new
  @output_buffer.safe_append='Hello
  '.freeze
  @output_buffer.append=  helper.form_for(model) do |f|
    @output_buffer.safe_append='
    '.freeze
    @output_buffer.append=( f.text_field :name )
    @output_buffer.safe_append='
    '.freeze
  end 
  @output_buffer.safe_append='World
  '.freeze
  @output_buffer.to_s
ensure
  @virtual_path, @output_buffer = _old_virtual_path, _old_output_buffer
end
```

I think the problem is the use of `@output_buffer` in the block, but I'm not 100% sure: even if the same buffer is used, the block's content will duplicate, doesn't it? I'm still missing something, hence I'm going to further debug this :)

